Before analysing the data

  • Individual dataframes joined
  • Splitting cells containing multiple variables
  • Convert strings to numbers
  • Grouping numerical varibales in intervals
  • Ensuring that all variables are correctly classified

Identifying and visualising trends with ggplot

Prostatic acid phosphatase and cause of death

  • PA phosphatase levels are increased in patients with bone metastases
  • PA phosphatase levels are higher in patients that die from cancer

Tumor size and bone metastases

  • Tumors are larger in patients that have died from prostate cancer
  • Tumors are larger in patients with metastases

Serum hemoglobin and bone metastases

  • Serum hemoglobin levels are higher in patients without metastases
  • Serum hemoglobin levels drop with increased age

Status and bone metastases

  • Risk of dying from prostate cancer doubles if the cancer spreads from the prostate

Activity and bone metastases

  • The activity level is affected by disease progress
  • Bone metastases leads to reduced activity

Estrogen dose and status

  • Estrogen is important for survival if the cancer has spread
  • High estrogen dose has a negetive effect as age increase

Seahwaâ€™s tumor size boxplotâ€¦

  • The prostate cancer was the second highest cause of death.
  • The stages of the prostate cancer did not make significant difference in the tumor size.

Predictive models and ANN

Linear regression of blood pressure

  • The only linear regression model that fit well was for systolic blood pressure vs diastolic blood pressure, grouped by cause of death
  • The best fit is for patients that have died from respiratory disease

Predicting death cause with logistic regression

  • The most important predictors for predicting if a patient died from prostate cancer (determined from ANOVA) were stage/grade index and prostatic acid phosphatase levels
  • 5-fold cross validation gave a model accuracy of 74.5%

PCA analysis shows if the data groups based on all the variables

  • A PCA analysis is carried out to search for groupings and patterns of the data based on all variables

The plot shows the variance explained by the different principal components

Clustering

Identifying clustering with PCA

  • PCA analysis is not will suited for this data, since a single PCA cannot explain a lot of the variance levels
  • PC #1 explains 22.5% of the variance

Identifying clustering with PCA

  • No clear clusters could be identified
  • The best clusters are found when stratifying by status and if a person died from prostate cancer

======= ## Conclusions - Prostatic acid (PA) phosphatase levels are higher in patients with metastases and have died from prostate cancer - The risk of dying from prostate cancer increases with larger tumors - Serum hemoglobin levels are lower in older patients with bone metastases - When the cancer has metastasized the patients are less active and there is a much bigger risk of dying - High doses of estrogen have negative effects for older patients - Logistic regression can predict with 75% accuracy if a patient have died from prostate cancer, with the most important predictors being stage/grade index and PA phosphatase levels - ANN conclusion hereâ€¦â€¦ - The data has no clearly seperated clusters
